==English==
===Etymology===
From ''The Scarlet Pimpernel,'' [[rescuer]] of [[aristocrat|aristocrats]] from the French [[revolutionist|revolutionists]] in the [[novel]] ''[[wikipedia:The Scarlet Pimpernel|The Scarlet Pimpernel]]'' (1905) by Baroness Emmuska Orczy.
===Noun===
'''pimpernel'''
# A [[gallant]] dashing resourceful [[man]] given to remarkable [[feat|feats]] of [[bravery]] and [[derring-do]] in liberating [[victim|victims]] of [[tyranny]] and [[injustice]].
#: ''Lined up solidly with the ''Pimpernels'' and with the persecuted.'' -- Hal Lehrman
